data.description: A true Must See..Corner Lot, Cul De Sac, homes sits on 1.17 acres nestled in the Hobbs Creek Subdivision. Walking distance to Cedar Creek Middle School & Intermediate. Also, 10 minute drive to the new Camino Real Elementary School or Cedar Creek High. Safe, quiet, peaceful neighborhood home has 150k in upgrades (list will be provided at showing). Numerous flower beds and landscaping with ideal lighting in entryways, bushes, trees house facades and architectural features (15k). Custom entry iron door& matching office barn iron door as well (10k). Complete entry wood dining room with full on tavern swinging wood doors at bar/cantina area(35K). Garage offers option to convert to apartment with attic loft, mini split ac already hooked up & power for amenities optional (15k). Kitchen offers custom salt water fish tank with huge butler's pantry & cabinets have Walnut fronts (50k).Upscale appliances. Enjoy 2 fireplaces, indoor natural burning wood or outdoor propane fireplace on 1000 sq ft deck with different elevations (85k). Skylight lighting throughout entire home(10k) custom master bath offers sauna system(10k) & custom closet with matching column vanities plus touch mirrors(25k). Tile throughout entire home, no carpet! There is no other home in Bastrop county quite like this. Too many upgrades to mention. YOU HAVE TO SEE! Home owned by Owner of Immaculate Tile https://youtu.be/kE9doFac1EU  Showing requires appt. Not vacant, pets on premises. Bastrop CAD Values at $537,886 without upgrades. 15 mins from ABIA, easy commute to Austin, Tesla, I30, 183. Low tax rate.
